        // We use BFS/Dijkstra-like approach where the state includes the count of heavy edges.

        // dist[i][j] stores the minimum number of edges required to reach node i having used exactly j heavy edges.
        // Since we only care about reachability (existence), a simpler BFS state tracking is sufficient.

